{0 Kot}

[kot] is an OCaml library that offers an implementation
of {b persistent catenable deques}.
It is based on the paper
{{: http://www.aladdin.cs.cmu.edu/papers/pdfs/y2000/catenable.pdf} Simple Confluently Persistent Catenable Lists}
by Haim Kaplan, Chris Okasaki, and Robert E. Tarjan (2000).
It is also described in the paper
{{: https://cambium.inria.fr/~fpottier/publis/ponsonnet-pottier-kot.pdf} Verified Persistent Catenable Deques}
by Juliette Ponsonnet and Fran√ßois Pottier (2025).


{1 API}

The main module is {!Kot.Deque}.

{1 Installation and Usage}

Type [opam install kot].

In your [dune] file, add [(libraries kot)] to the description of
your [library] or [executable].
